any tips for getting kids motivated for school ok we started off the summer with great intentions reading lists summer workbooks camps educational visits to museums etc but now it has all boiled down to video games tv shows and sleeping in the morning yikes i worry that my kids are not going to be focused on their studies this year any pearls of wisdom from experienced parents or kids who have 'been there' will be greatly appreciated it sounds like you're doing the right thing naturally most kids even if they don't admit it are a bit bored by weeks of tv and video games so they will probably actually be quite excited to get back to school and start having a more varied life again i know it always made me look forward to school when a few days before my mum would take me out shopping for stationery i always liked to start a new school year with new stationery Homeschooling SpongeBob SquarePants Little Britain EastEnders The Apprentice 3 One Tree Hill (TV series) The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie The Fairly OddParents Education Social rule Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide About a Boy The Adventures of Pete & Pete Teachers (film) I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Girls Aloud AFI 100 Years series Shaggy dog story Graduate school Our Gang Play School Roxette Theory of conduct Animal Crossing Pok__mon (anime) WCBS-FM Infantilism MTV2 Cindy Sheehan Attack on Pearl Harbor Music Douglas Adams The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Marching band The Star Wars Holiday Special The Legend of Zelda series characters The Contender (television series) The Critic USS Yorktown (CV-10) Intelligent design movement Richard Feynman Baseball Spy Kids Daylight saving time Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The Catcher in the Rye Weezer The Ashlee Simpson Show Emo Spot the Dog They Might Be Giants Sesame Street Wargaming Survivor (TV series) Summer Homecoming (tradition) The Late Show with David Letterman The Lovely Bones Video game developer Super Mario Bros. television series Kender 